The paper deals with a graph optimization problem, specifically the Linear Arrangement Problem, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper also discusses parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
